{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S6 â€” Apply the GitHub mirror lock (repo-level ruleset, deploy-key-only push)\n\n## Why\nEnforce that GitHub `main` can ONLY be advanced by the Gerrit replication deploy key. The lock\nis a REPO-LEVEL ruleset (navapbc is a free org -> admin-proof ORG-level rulesets need a paid\nplan; trusted-admin editability is the accepted risk, recorded in S6-pre's ADR). Applies the\nlock that S6-pre prepared (snapshot + ADR + backend/token). Proven empirically (derisk): an\nactive repo-level ruleset with deploy-key-only bypass REJECTS a repo-admin's direct push\n(`GH013`), so \"no human/admin bypass\" holds.\n\n## What\n- **Use the native provider (peer-pattern simplification).** `terraform-provider-github`\n  **v6.8.0 (Nov 2025, PR #2726)** added native `DeployKey` bypass support (removed the\n  actor_type whitelist; made `actor_id` optional). So the whole prior `null_resource` + `gh api`\n  + `ignore_changes` + disabled->active two-phase dance is **dropped** â€” it existed only because\n  the provider rejected `DeployKey`. Pin `integrations/github >= 6.8.0`.\n- One `github_repository_ruleset` for the branch lock on `main` (+ any other branch the bot\n  pushes), created directly at `enforcement = \"active\"` in a single apply, with rules\n  `update` + `creation` + `deletion` + `non_fast_forward` and a single\n  `bypass_actors { actor_type = \"DeployKey\"  bypass_mode = \"always\" }` (NO `actor_id` â€” it's\n  optional; GitHub normalizes to `null`, which the empirical spike confirmed is canonical and\n  accepted). A SEPARATE `github_repository_ruleset` for tags (`refs/tags/**`, target `tag`) with\n  the same rules + the same DeployKey bypass (else tag pushes are rejected).\n- **Replace the existing `main-protection` ruleset** (DERISK E5: id 18048287, PR +\n  required-status-checks model â€” incompatible with deploy-key-only push). It is snapshotted in\n  S6-pre; S6 deletes it (`gh api -X DELETE` or via the provider after `terraform import`) and\n  creates the mirror-lock rulesets. There is no PR/status-check ruleset left once S6 applies.\n- Consume S5's deploy key via a `data \"github_repository_deploy_key\"` (or a remote-state ref to\n  S5's `deploy_key_id` output) so the dependency is explicit and S6 cannot apply before S5's key\n  exists. (The bypass entry itself carries no actor_id; the data-source lookup is the existence\n  gate, failing the apply loudly if the key is absent.)\n- **Token scope.** The Terraform identity needs `Administration: write` on `navapbc/rebar`\n  (fine-grained PAT scoped to this repo, or classic `repo`), injected at apply time as a\n  `sensitive` var from a CI secret, never committed to `.tfvars`.\n- **Remote state.** `infra/terraform/github.tf` uses the shared remote backend with state\n  locking; `terraform plan` is reviewed before every `apply`.\n- Mirror hygiene: turn OFF Pull Requests (Feb-2026 repo setting), disable Issues + Actions; add\n  a \"mirror â€” contribute via Gerrit at rebar.solutions.navateam.com\" banner to the About +\n  README; do NOT archive (archiving freezes the replication bot too).\n- Rollback (runnable in ~15 min): set the rulesets `enforcement = disabled` (provider apply, or\n  `gh api PATCH .../rulesets/{id} -f enforcement=disabled` for speed), restore `main-protection`\n  from S6-pre's snapshot, and re-enable PRs/Issues/Actions.\n\n## Scope\nIn: the two native ruleset resources (branch + tag) with DeployKey bypass, replacing\nmain-protection, mirror hygiene, rollback. Out: the snapshot/ADR/token-scope pre-work (S6-pre);\nthe Gerrit-side replication (S5); the end-to-end push-past-the-ruleset proof (S7).\n**Dependency:** apply AFTER S6-pre (snapshot + ADR + backend ready) AND S5 (deploy key exists).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/github.tf` â€” provider pin (`>= 6.8.0`), remote backend, sensitive token var,\n  the two `github_repository_ruleset` resources (branch + tag, `enforcement = active`, DeployKey\n  bypass), the `data.github_repository_deploy_key` lookup, and the repo-feature toggles\n  (PRs/Issues/Actions off, mirror banner).\n- (optional) a small documented step to delete the pre-existing `main-protection` ruleset by id\n  (or `terraform import` then replace), referencing S6-pre's snapshot.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A direct `git push` / PR-merge to `main` by a non-bypass identity is REJECTED; force-push\n      and deletion of `main` are REJECTED. (Empirically confirmed for the admin-push case.)\n- [ ] A tag push by a non-bypass identity is REJECTED by the separate `refs/tags/**` ruleset.\n- [ ] The DeployKey bypass is expressed natively as `bypass_actors { actor_type = \"DeployKey\"\n      bypass_mode = \"always\" }` (no `actor_id`) via `terraform-provider-github >= 6.8.0`, and is\n      the ONLY bypass entry on each ruleset; re-running `terraform apply` is idempotent with no\n      perpetual diff (provider stores `actor_id = null`, matching GitHub's normalization).\n- [ ] The rulesets are created at `enforcement = \"active\"` in a single apply (NO null_resource,\n      NO gh-api bypass step, NO disabled->active two-phase dance, NO `ignore_changes`).\n- [ ] S6 obtains the deploy key via a data source / remote-state ref (not a hand-copied ID);\n      applying before S5's key exists fails loudly.\n- [ ] The pre-existing `main-protection` ruleset (PR + required-status-checks) is replaced/removed\n      (snapshot kept in S6-pre); no PR/status-check ruleset remains on `main`.\n- [ ] PRs disabled, Issues disabled, Actions disabled; README/About carry the mirror banner;\n      repo NOT archived.\n- [ ] The Terraform identity's `Administration: write` scope is documented and injected as a\n      `sensitive` var from a CI secret (never in `.tfvars`); `github.tf` uses the shared remote\n      backend with locking.\n- [ ] A rollback runnable in ~15 min is documented (set `enforcement=disabled`, restore\n      `main-protection` from the S6-pre snapshot, re-enable PRs/Issues/Actions)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782699635407239001,"uuid":"3bb49d8d-2c4b-4184-b79d-7c356c340d53"}